# Sync Engine System

The Sync Engine ensures data consistency across devices and offline usage.

It is critical for reliability.

---

# Product Vision

Sync Engine must:

- support offline-first usage
- synchronize data reliably
- resolve conflicts intelligently
- prevent data loss
- maintain cross-device consistency

---

# Architecture

SyncController

↓

SyncState

↓

SyncQueueManager

↓

ConflictResolver

↓

Remote API + Local DB

---

# State Management

SyncState includes:

- idle
- syncing
- queued
- failed
- resolved

Core Data:

- pendingChanges
- syncedItems
- conflictItems
- retryQueue

---

# Sync Strategy

- optimistic local updates
- background sync
- queued retries
- exponential backoff

---

# Conflict Resolution

Rules:

- last-write-wins (default)
- AI-assisted merge (future)
- manual resolution fallback

---

# Offline Behaviour

- full offline support
- queue all actions locally
- sync when connection restored

---

# Data Sources

Sync applies to:

- Notes
- Bookmarks
- Progress
- Profile changes
- Settings

---

# API Contracts

POST /sync/push

GET /sync/pull

POST /sync/conflict-resolve

---

# Analytics Events

sync_started

sync_completed

sync_failed

conflict_detected

conflict_resolved

---

# UX Rules

- sync must be invisible
- only show errors when necessary
- never block user actions

---

# Performance

- sync must not block UI
- batch network requests
- minimize payload size

---

# Reliability Rules

- retry failed sync automatically
- preserve local state at all times
- never overwrite local data without confirmation

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Queue manager

Conflict resolver

Sync state transitions

Integration Tests:

Offline → online sync flow

Conflict resolution flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating sync features:

- always implement offline-first behavior
- always queue local actions
- always handle conflicts safely
- never block UI on sync operations